  "bench_knowledge": [
    "Thiol-based reducing agents (DTT, \u03b2-mercaptoethanol) are rapidly oxidised by dissolved O\u2082 in aqueous buffers. At 4\u00b0C in standard buffer, DTT has an effective half-life of approximately 1 week; at room temperature in air-exposed buffer, this drops to hours. For critical applications (disulfide bond reduction, enzyme protection), the stock should be made fresh on the day of use."
